<p>&quot;I did it.&quot; </p><p>Malloy called for federal action to restrict some weapons.</p><p>Connecticut has an assault weapons ban on the books, but &quot;in the absence of a federal framework … no state would be safe based on its own laws,&quot; Malloy said. &quot;That's why a [federal] assault weapons ban was so very important.&quot; </p><p>&quot;I'm a big believer in hunting rights, a big believer in the second amendment, but the reality is that this has gone too far,&quot; the Democratic governor said.</p><p>The White House <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/dec/17/white-house-obama-gun-control-newtown\">promised a comprehensive series of measures</a>, including gun control legislation, on Monday to prevent similar mass shootings.</p><p>Malloy said a statewide moment of silence would be observed on Friday, 21 December at 9.30am, exactly a week after the massacre began. He called on houses of worship to ring their bells 26 times for the victims killed inside the school. The gunman, Adam Lanza, also killed his mother Nancy in their home.</p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/401240866|2012-12-22T11:49:03Z|3aa6dc25f3a69a9d45b9d9a2cd295bf6a2f908fa -->","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2012-12-17T22:36:49Z","hasStoryPackage":"true","score":"1.0","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/12/17/1355781273418/Dannel-Malloy-newtown-003.jpg","standfirst":"Overcome with emotion after a funeral in Newtown, governor calls for state to observe moment of silence on Friday morning<br /><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-news-blog/2012/dec/17/newtown-shootings-funerals-victims-live\">Follow live developments on the Newtown school shooting</a>","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3ct9b","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/12/17/1355781273418/Dannel-Malloy-newtown-003.jpg","wordcount":"339","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"40124086